reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 16, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wish we had these in the U.S.
reviews.reviewText: I use tissues all freaking day long -- for allergies, makeup, blotting excess chapstick, you name it. I can't tell you how many times I've wished for a travel-style tissue pack that I could toss in my suitcase when going on vacation, or keep in my car's glove box, etc., that would actually hold a decent number of tissues. This might sound crazy to the tissue manufacturers of the world, but sometimes, people actually want to have more than 10 tissues on hand, but also don't want to lug around an entire cardboard box of them that doesn't fit anywhere. Crazy stuff, I know.This product is exactly what I've been looking for. One pack of these easily lasted an entire week when I went on vacation recently, and I've kept another pack in my car and the third on my desk at work. The tissues are soft (though I've never been especially fussy about tissue softness and never purchase the ones that come with added lotion or whatever, so if that kind of thing is important to you please take my opinion with a grain of salt), and don't feel especially thin or cheap even though they're only 1-ply. I never had them rip on me unexpectedly or anything. The portability-to-quantity ratio is perfect, and as far as I'm concerned, this is a new travel necessity for me. Unfortunately, until Kleenex and Puffs get it through their heads that us uncultured American tissue consumers might like to see these on our store shelves as well, I'm stuck buying these Korean ones through Amazon, I guess. At least the packaging is cute.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect purse tissues
reviews.reviewText: I carry these around in my medium sized purse and they are very handy. The packaging is so cute and has a convenient opening to grab one tissue at a time. Tissues are full size and work great for allergy sniffles. They are soft and don’t fall apart. I hope these never go out of stock!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 29, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Full size Kleenex in a easy to carry pouch
reviews.reviewText: Why why why is it so hard to find full size Kleenex in travel sizes? The last thing I want when I have a runny nose is to try to unfold a crappy tiny piece of paper that will not hold my snot. It’s ridiculous and I will pay crazy amounts of money to buy this product which appears to be imported from Korea because they have priorities when it comes to on the go snot. Plus the packaging is very cute.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Perfect size but light sniffles only!
reviews.reviewText: The designs are cute and fit perfect in my car and medium sized purses. While these work great for teary eyes and sniffles, they were a little lightweight for my severe allergy days of really blowing my nose. On those days I had to grab 2-3 tissues then blow my nose to prevent leakage (TMI).
